#. Tag: date
#: man-cheatmake.1.docbook:8
#, no-c-format
msgid "2003-03-08"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: manvolnum
#: man-cheatmake.1.docbook:13
#, no-c-format
msgid "<manvolnum>1</manvolnum>"
msgstr "<manvolnum>1</manvolnum>"

#. Tag: refpurpose
#: man-cheatmake.1.docbook:18
#, no-c-format
msgid "fool <command>make</command> into not rebuilding certain files"
msgstr ""
"Käsu <command>make</command> libavariant teatud failide ehitamatajätmiseks"

#. Tag: cmdsynopsis
#: man-cheatmake.1.docbook:22
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<command>cheatmake</command> <group><option>hidechange</option> "
"<replaceable>file</replaceable></group> <group><option>show</option></group> "
"<group><option>why</option> <replaceable>file</replaceable></group>"
msgstr ""
"<command>cheatmake</command> <group><option>hidechange</option> "
"<replaceable>fail</replaceable></group> <group><option>show</option></group> "
"<group><option>why</option> <replaceable>fail</replaceable></group>"

#. Tag: title
#: man-cheatmake.1.docbook:32
#, no-c-format
msgid "Description"
msgstr "Kirjeldus"

#. Tag: para
#: man-cheatmake.1.docbook:34
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<command>cheatmake</command> is used to save time when recompiling. It can "
"fool make into skipping files that haven't changed in a meaningful way. This "
"can be used for instance when you change a comment in a file but none of the "
"actual code."
msgstr ""
"<command>cheatmake</command> aitab säästa aega ümberkompileerimisel. See "
"petab ära käsu make ja laseb sel vahele jätta failid, mis ei ole mingeid "
"erilisi muutusi üle elanud. Seda saab kasutada näiteks siis, kui muudad "
"failis kommentaari, aga mitte tegelikku koodi."

#. Tag: para
#: man-cheatmake.1.docbook:39
#, no-c-format
msgid "This utility is part of the &kde; Software Development Kit."
msgstr "See utiliit kuulub &kde; tarkvaraarenduse komplekti koosseisu."

#. Tag: title
#: man-cheatmake.1.docbook:44
#, no-c-format
msgid "Options"
msgstr "Võtmed"

#. Tag: term
#: man-cheatmake.1.docbook:48
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>hidechange</option> <replaceable>file</replaceable>"
msgstr "<option>hidechange</option> <replaceable>fail</replaceable>"

#. Tag: para
#: man-cheatmake.1.docbook:49
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Hides the fact that file was changed by setting the timestamp into the past. "
"Use with care!"
msgstr ""
"Peidab tõsiasja, et faili on muudetud, määrates selle ajatempli varsemaks. "
"Kasuta seda võimalust äärmise ettevaatusega!"

#. Tag: option
#: man-cheatmake.1.docbook:53
#, no-c-format
msgid "show"
msgstr "show"

#. Tag: para
#: man-cheatmake.1.docbook:54
#, no-c-format
msgid "Lists what files <command>make</command> currently needs to rebuild"
msgstr ""
"Näitab failide nimekirja, mida <command>make</command> peab ümber ehitama."

#. Tag: term
#: man-cheatmake.1.docbook:57
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>why</option> <replaceable>file</replaceable>"
msgstr "<option>why</option> <replaceable>fail</replaceable>"

#. Tag: para
#: man-cheatmake.1.docbook:58
#, no-c-format
msgid "Explains why make must rebuild file"
msgstr "Selgitab, miks make peab faili ümber ehitama."

#. Tag: title
#: man-cheatmake.1.docbook:64
#, no-c-format
msgid "Environment"
msgstr "Keskkond"

#. Tag: para
#: man-cheatmake.1.docbook:66
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"One of the following variables (but not both) should be set if the source "
"directory is different from the build directory. If the build directory is "
"simply a subdirectory of the source directory, the simpler variable "
"<envar>OBJ_SUBDIR</envar> should be used."
msgstr ""
"Kui lähtekataloog on ehituskataloogist erinev, tuleb määrata üks (aga mitte "
"mõlemad) järgnevatest muutujatest. Kui ehituskataloog on lihtsalt "
"lähtekataloogi alamkataloog, tuleks kasutada lihtsamat muutujat "
"<envar>OBJ_SUBDIR</envar>."

#. Tag: envar
#: man-cheatmake.1.docbook:73
#, no-c-format
msgid "OBJ_SUBJDIR"
msgstr "OBJ_SUBJDIR"

#. Tag: para
#: man-cheatmake.1.docbook:74
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Indicates that the build directory is in the given subdirectory of the "
"source directory. For instance, if the source directory is <filename class="
"\"directory\">kdesdk</filename> and the build directory is <filename class="
"\"directory\">kdesdk/obj-i386-linux</filename>, then <envar>OBJ_SUBDIR</"
"envar> should be set to <parameter>obj-i386-linux</parameter>."
msgstr ""
"Osutab, et ehituskataloog on lähtekataloogi määratud alamkataloog. Kui "
"näiteks lähtekataloog on <filename class=\"directory\">kdesdk</filename> ja "
"ehituskataloog <filename class=\"directory\">kdesdk/obj-i386-linux</"
"filename>, tuleb <envar>OBJ_SUBDIR</envar> väärtuseks määrata <parameter>obj-"
"i386-linux</parameter>."

#. Tag: envar
#: man-cheatmake.1.docbook:77
#, no-c-format
msgid "OBJ_REPLACEMENT"
msgstr "OBJ_REPLACEMENT"

#. Tag: para
#: man-cheatmake.1.docbook:78
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A <command>sed</command> expression that is used to transform the source "
"directory into the build directory. For instance, if the source directory is "
"<filename class=\"directory\">kdesdk/obj-i386-linux</filename>, then "
"<envar>OBJ_REPLACEMENT</envar> should be set to <parameter>s#kdesdk#kdesdk-"
"obj#</parameter>."
msgstr ""
"<command>sed</command>-avaldis, millega teisendatakse lähtekataloog "
"ehituskataloogiks. Kui näiteks lähtekataloog on <filename class=\"directory"
"\">kdesdk/obj-i386-linux</filename>, tuleb <envar>OBJ_REPLACEMENT</envar> "
"väärtuseks määrata <parameter>s#kdesdk#kdesdk-obj#</parameter>."

#. Tag: title
#: man-cheatmake.1.docbook:86
#, no-c-format
msgid "See Also"
msgstr "Vaata ka"

